refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.returnvalues;
Un array que contiene las informaciones relativas al esquema, cuando el proceso se ha ejecutado con éxito.
&false; será devuelto si ocurre un error.

&reftitle.examples;
Ejemplo con PDO::cubrid_schema
Este ejemplo muestra cómo recuperar las claves primarias y extranjeras de la tabla "game".
<?php $pk_list = $dbh->cubrid_schema(PDO::CUBRID_SCH_PRIMARY_KEY, "game"); print_r($pk_list);
$fk_list = $dbh->cubrid_schema(PDO::CUBRID_SCH_IMPORTED_KEYS, "game"); print_r($fk_list); ?>
&example.outputs;
Resultado: Array ( [0] => Array ( [CLASS_NAME] => game [ATTR_NAME] => athlete_code [KEY_SEQ] => 3 [KEY_NAME] => pk_game_host_year_event_code_athlete_code )
[1] => Array ( [CLASS_NAME] => game [ATTR_NAME] => event_code [KEY_SEQ] => 2 [KEY_NAME] => pk_game_host_year_event_code_athlete_code )
[2] => Array ( [CLASS_NAME] => game [ATTR_NAME] => host_year [KEY_SEQ] => 1 [KEY_NAME] => pk_game_host_year_event_code_athlete_code )
) Array ( [0] => Array ( [PKTABLE_NAME] => athlete [PKCOLUMN_NAME] => code [FKTABLE_NAME] => game [FKCOLUMN_NAME] => athlete_code [KEY_SEQ] => 1 [UPDATE_RULE] => 1 [DELETE_RULE] => 1 [FK_NAME] => fk_game_athlete_code [PK_NAME] => pk_athlete_code )
[1] => Array ( [PKTABLE_NAME] => event [PKCOLUMN_NAME] => code [FKTABLE_NAME] => game [FKCOLUMN_NAME] => event_code [KEY_SEQ] => 1 [UPDATE_RULE] => 1 [DELETE_RULE] => 1 [FK_NAME] => fk_game_event_code [PK_NAME] => pk_event_code )
)
